{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place water into mixing bowl and insert simmering basket, weigh in quinoa and rinse <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Stir with aid of spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid to ensure a thorough rinsing.","Cook <nobr>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with spatula, transfer quinoa to a large bowl and allow to cool. Discard steaming water and dry mixing bowl.","Place parsley into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place olive oil, beans, mushrooms, onion, bell pepper, carrot, celery and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and chop a further <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then sauté <nobr>5 min\/250°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add reserved quinoa, reserved chopped parsley, panko, salt, pepper and egg and with aid of spatula mix <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Divide mixture and shape into eight equal-sized patties. Place onto a baking sheet and chill in freezer 10 minutes.","Heat approximately 2 tsp oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook four patties at a time, 2-3 minutes each side, or until heated through and browned. Transfer to a plate and keep warm. Cook remaining patties the same way using 2 tsp oil for frying. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["35 oz water","3 ½ oz quinoa","½ oz parsley, leaves and tender stems only","1 oz olive oil, plus 4 tsp to fry","15 oz canned garbanzo beans rinsed and drained (approx. 1 can)","6 oz fresh portobello mushrooms, sliced (approx. ½ in.)","4 oz yellow onion, quartered","2 oz red bell pepper, cut into pieces","2 oz carrot, cut into pieces","1 oz celery","3 garlic cloves","2 oz panko","½ tsp fine sea salt","½ tsp ground black pepper","1 large egg"]}],"id":"r156941","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-JZzqumr4OLc\/XZVQoJ4kp-I\/AAAAAAAAdDo\/8N7JQ3feFQEGZUgrqAIIwF1vkLBesF3ygCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_SydTkbyZGzlkjZv2.png","title":"Quinoa Patties","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7 g","fat":"6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"29 g","calories":"824 kJ \/ 197 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, plate, baking sheet, freezer, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["For an egg-free version, replace the egg with 1 tbsp flax seed mixed with 3 tbsp warm water. Whisk together and refrigerate 15 minutes before using.","To freeze uncooked patties: place patties between sheets of wax paper on a baking sheet and freeze. Wrap individually and store in a freezer bag or plastic container. Fry or grill as needed without thawing first.","Patties can be baked for 20 minutes at 400°F until lightly golden."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","8 portions"]}